channel.title: Money Making and Combat Training tips, care to help?
channel.description:
Lately i've been getting back into runescape, and it's been about two months from when I lost my partyhat and santa. But, the main question I want to ask is how should I make money? Without boxing, i've used this trick before and it lost me the items I mentioned above. Also, what about combat training? I'm level 113 with around 80 in attack, defence and strength. My methods don't seem to help anymore.
So please post to help me, and I will be thanking you with my greatest pleasure. If you want to add me, add Golden Bills (I used to have bills, lmao) and comment your name here so I know who you are. Thanks for your time reading this, it is much appreciated.
[center]-Pink Phat-[/center]

item.title: Money Making and Combat Training tips, care to help?
item.dc:creator: @judostar1 judostar1
item.description:
@judostar1 wrote:

killing any monster level 50+ is generally a good way to make money, except those spiders in the stronghold of security.

Generally good ways to make cash for PvM related:
F2p: kill cockroaches, lesser demons hill giants and moss giants.

P2p: Generally anything level 50+.

If you want to not do pvm, I recommend picking up limps in the hill giant dung, WC, mining or picking up white berries (risky since every so often there are noobish pkers)

slayer blows js. avrg profit ph if your lucky is 500k if that. you can make 2x that at a low combat level etc with a bit of the good old common sense and more if you have either good stats/good teams or willing to experiment.
[/quote]I enjoy being assigned tasks to do …so I don’t have to decide[/quote]
I’m not saying slayer isn’t fun, I’m just saying its crap for making gps;o. I do slayer all the time ;p but I do it purely for the fact it varies the npc’s you kill as killing the same can get boring etc. Slayers a good way to improve your combat knowledge of rs in a way, its a shame people don’t see the value of the skill but for gp making in slayer is not good ;p.
